<subSubSection id="07AF96B5FFF2FFDDF7F0661FFD4CCD05" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="258" pageId="22" pageNumber="257" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4F0AC53EFFF2FFDCF7F0661FFCC2C968" blockId="22.[676,1210,1547,1700]" box="[677,777,1547,1573]" pageId="22" pageNumber="257">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F0AC53EFFF2FFDDF7F0663EFD4CCD05" blockId="22.[676,1210,1547,1700]" lastBlockId="23.[111,649,216,591]" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="258" pageId="22" pageNumber="257">
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF2FFDCF7F0663EFCAAC90F" authority="Werff, 2013" authorityName="van der Werff" authorityYear="2013" box="[677,865,1578,1604]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="22" pageNumber="257" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ivohibensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF2FFDCF7F0663EFCAAC90F" box="[677,865,1578,1604]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="257">Ocotea ivohibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="66F2A457FFF2FFDCF63D663FFC71C90E" box="[872,954,1579,1605]" pageId="22" pageNumber="257" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has been confused with 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF2FFDCF7F1665EFCB6C92F" authority="Baker" authorityName="Baker" box="[676,893,1610,1636]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="22" pageNumber="257" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichantha">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF2FFDCF7F1665EFCFCC92F" box="[676,823,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="257">O. trichantha</emphasis>
Baker
</taxonomicName>
from which it differs as follows: 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF2FFDCF7B5667EFC51C9C8" authority="Werff, 2013" authorityName="van der Werff" authorityYear="2013" box="[736,922,1641,1668]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="22" pageNumber="257" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ivohibensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF2FFDCF7B5667EFC51C9C8" box="[736,922,1641,1668]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="257">Ocotea ivohibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="66F2A457FFF2FFDCF6CA667EFC24C9CF" box="[927,1007,1642,1668]" pageId="22" pageNumber="257" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has sparsely pubescent flowers (densely pubescent in 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF2FFDCF14E669EFB62C9E8" box="[1051,1193,1673,1700]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="22" pageNumber="257" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichantha">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF2FFDCF14E669EFB62C9E8" box="[1051,1193,1673,1700]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="257">O. trichantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), domatia covered with reddish hairs (white hairs in 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF3FFDDF52560ECFF3ECE5A" box="[112,245,247,274]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="23" pageNumber="258" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichantha">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF3FFDDF52560ECFF3ECE5A" box="[112,245,247,274]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="258">O. trichantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the major veins slightly impressed on the upper leaf surface (immersed in 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF3FFDDF75A610CFF58CE1A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="23" pageNumber="258" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichantha">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF3FFDDF75A610CFF58CE1A" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="258">O. trichantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In the older collection made by 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF3FFDDF4AC6123FD95CE1A" authorityName="Wahl &amp; Sime" authorityYear="2002" box="[505,606,311,337]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Humbert" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Humbert</taxonomicName>
the hairs covering the domatia have largely fallen off; leaf shape, venation and the sparse indument on the flowers allow identification as 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF3FFDDF4A76182FD43CEFB" authority="Werff, 2013" authorityName="van der Werff" authorityYear="2013" box="[498,648,406,432]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="23" pageNumber="258" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ivohibensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF3FFDDF4A76182FD43CEFB" box="[498,648,406,432]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="258">O. ivohibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="66F2A457FFF3FFDDF52661A2FF0ECE9B" box="[115,197,438,464]" pageId="23" pageNumber="258" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The indument on the lower leaf surface of 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF3FFDDF52461C2FEC9CEA4" authority="Werff, 2013" authorityName="van der Werff" authorityYear="2013" box="[113,258,469,496]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="23" pageNumber="258" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ivohibensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF3FFDDF52461C2FEC9CEA4" box="[113,258,469,496]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="258">O. ivohibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="66F2A457FFF3FFDDF45C61C2FE91CEBB" box="[265,346,470,496]" pageId="23" pageNumber="258" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is variable. Some specimens have a sparse indument of erect hairs on the lamina, others have only some hairs along the major veins or are glabrous with the exception of the domatia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
